    {
      "type": "text",
      "title": "About This Example Set",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 12,
        "w": 10,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 4
      },
      "id": 1,
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "## Service Health Monitoring\n\nThis example shows how the **Datatable Panel** turns a table of service metrics into an interactive monitoring dashboard.\n\n### Features demonstrated\n\n- \ud83d\udfe5 **Row coloring** \u2014 whole row turns red when any metric is critical\n- \ud83d\udcca **Cell coloring** \u2014 Latency cells colored by threshold independently\n- \ud83d\udd17 **Clickthrough** \u2014 click any service name to open a detail view\n- \ud83d\udc41\ufe0f **Hidden columns** \u2014 service ID is hidden but passed in the URL\n- \ud83d\udd0d **Search** \u2014 type in the search box to filter services\n\n### Try it\n\n1. Look at the table on the right \u2014 notice the color coding\n2. Click a **service name** to drill into that service\n3. The detail dashboard opens with the service pre-selected\n\n[Open Overview \u2192](/d/dt-service-health-overview)",
        "code": {
          "language": "plaintext",
          "showLineNumbers": false,
          "showMiniMap": false
        }
      },
      "targets": []
    },
